emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated, Beatrice Twyman and Margaret West Watson; standing: Arthur C. Holloway and Gloria Golden Grate, gathered at table to discuss the DI Club and Greater Pittsburgh Improvement League (GPIL) Frappe Sip
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 22, 1961, pg. A13 reads: "Mapping Plans - The Original D.I. Club is "delightfully insane" with enthusiasm, as the members discuss plans for the crowning of "Miss GPIL." Left to right, seated: Beatrice Twyman, GPIL chairman, and Margaret West Watson, Original D.I. Club president.  Standing: Juanita Drake, a D.I.; Arthur C. Holloway, president of the GPIL, and Gloria Grate, also a D.I. - Harris Photo."
